&lt;p&gt;Chemotherapy Scheduler (Countywide Post)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;32 hours per week (will consider hours worked across either 4 or 5 days)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and highly motivated individual with excellent communication, inter-personal and organisational skills to work as a chemotherapy scheduler and administrator within the chemotherapy units.  The post holder will join a busy team and will be a point of contact for patients and representatives attending for chemotherapy.  You will also be expected to act as part of the wider administration team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have some understanding of delivering on an aspect of a service within an administrative role and have an understanding of the cancer pathways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be the requirement to cross cover colleagues on other hospital sites so the successful candidate will need to be willing to travel when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;To discuss the role further, please contact Gaynor Jenkins, Directorate Support Manager, on ext 30042 or &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;gaynor.jenkins1@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
